y^2=\left( \frac{x}{ \sqrt{1+x^2}} \right)^2\Leftrightarrow
y^2=\frac{x^2}{1+x^2} \Leftrightarrow
y^2 (1+x^2)=x^2 \Leftrightarrow
y^2 +y^2x^2=x^2 \Leftrightarrow y^2=x^2- y^2x^2 \Leftrightarrow y^2=x^2 (1- y^2) \Leftrightarrow
x^2=\frac{y^2}{1- y^2} 
